@node USAGE "Usage of Erase"
 Erase can only be used from a Shell. Workbench 2 or higher is required.
 
 Erase has the following argument template:
 
                           FILE/M/A,TIMES/K/N

 FILE: The file, directory or wildcard which to erase. Multiple files are
       supported, at least one must be given.

 TIMES: The number of times that you want the file overwritten with data.
       Default is once.

 @{u}Examples@{uu}:
 
 Erase RAM:T RAM:ENV TIMES=2
 => Erases the contents of RAM:T and RAM:ENV, overwritting the files twice.
 
 Erase #?.(JPG|JPEG)
 => Erases all jpeg files in the current directory
@endnode
